<!-- File syntax:

    All tags are contained in <soundmap> tag. 
    
    For each file there is a <file> tag. 
    Its attribute 'name' tells the engine where to
    load it from, relative to original data files root.
    
    Each file contains a number of samples.
    
    For each sample there is a <sample> tag. Its attribute
    'sym' tells the engine which event this sample is for.
    
    If a sample is used in several events, those extra events
    are put into additional <alias> tags in the <sample> tag.

    You can find all SoundSymbols (values of 'sym' attribute) 
    known to the ufo2000 engine in the src/sound.cpp file 
    
    http://lxnt.info:8888/repos/ufo2k/trunk/src/sound.cpp
        
    You can download playcat program to play the ufo .cat files
    at http://lxnt.info/stuff/playcat.exe
    
    It plays both original and collector's edition files.
    It outputs a numerated index of the cat file so that you 
    can easily update this file. Please do. Send updated versions
    to the ufo2000 mailing list at ufo2000@lxnt.info.
    
    Source : http://lxnt.info/stuff/playcat.c
    Requires Allegro 4.0 DLL : http://lxnt.info/stuff/alleg40.dll
    
    You can test edited soundmap.xml file by setting F_SOUNDCHECK flag to 1
    in the ufo2000.ini file and launching the ufo2000.
    It will print all loaded  sounds and play each once.
-->

